<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Key Features to Look For</h2>

<p>Not all dictionary apps are equal. Here are the features that separate a great Scrabble dictionary from a basic word checker:</p>

<div class="space-y-3 my-6">
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Anagram Solving</span> — Enter tiles, get all valid words. Essential for rack study and finding bingos you might miss.
  </div>
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Wildcard/Blank Support</span> — Use ? or * for blank tiles. Lets you explore what words are possible with your actual rack.
  </div>
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Hook Display</span> — Shows which letters can be added before or after a word. Critical for extending plays on the board.
  </div>
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Offline Mode</span> — Full dictionary available without internet. Necessary for tournament venues and travel.
  </div>
  <div class="p-3 rounded border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <span class="font-semibold text-purple-300">Definitions</span> — Meaning alongside validity. Helps build vocabulary and understand words you're playing.
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Offline vs Online — When Each Matters</h2>

<p>Tournament players need offline access because phones are banned during games but used between rounds for study. Online apps suit casual home play where connectivity is not an issue and cloud sync keeps your data safe.</p>

<div class="p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10 my-6">
  <p class="text-sm text-indigo-400 font-medium mb-1">💡 Pro Tip</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Download your dictionary app's word list for offline use before tournament day. Nothing is worse than being unable to study during breaks because venue Wi-Fi is unreliable.</p>
</div>

<p>Online-only apps like web-based checkers have the advantage of always being up-to-date when new words are added to official dictionaries. The latest CSW updates happen annually, and online tools reflect changes immediately.</p>

